extension of second model: problem statement¶

In our research on fire location rescue time, we found that some of the incident can't be can be rescued within a certain amount of distance. Therefore, we plot the incident locations and then choose among candidate fire station locations to suggest the spot to build new stations.

The candidate fire station location is selected using the street data. It contains the list of road names in each district in the city.

# satisfied, unsatidfied, and station built
def return_XY(df):
    X = []
    Y = []
    for i in range(len(df)):
        wgs84aX = df["wgs84aX"].iloc[i]
        wgs84aY = df["wgs84aY"].iloc[i]
        X.append(wgs84aX)
        Y.append(wgs84aY)
    return X, Y


def station_location(df_list, city_name):

    legend_name = ["brigade 1", "brigade 2", "brigade 3", "brigade 4", "brigade 5", "brigade 6", "brigade 7"]
    color = ["springgreen", "lightgreen", "plum", "lightblue", "cyan", "aliceblue", "lightpink"]
    conversion = {'桃園市': "Taoyuan City", "臺北市": "Taipei City", "新北市": "New Taipei City", "基隆市": "Keelung City"}
    legend_name = ["brigade 1", "brigade 2", "brigade 3", "brigade 4", "brigade 5", "brigade 6", "brigade 7"]
    
    station_x, station_Y = return_XY(df_station)
    cluster_station = [Point(xy) for xy in zip(station_x, station_Y)]
    geopt_cluster4 = gp.GeoDataFrame(df_station, geometry=cluster_station)
    gdf_district_northern = gdf_district[gdf_district.COUNTYNAME.isin([city_name])]
    ax = gdf_district_northern.plot()
    patches = []
    for i in range(len(df_list)):
        gdf_district_northern[gdf_district_northern.TOWNNAME.isin(df_list[i])].plot(edgecolor=u'gray', color=color[i], ax=ax)
        patches.append(mpatches.Patch(color=color[i], label=legend_name[i]))
    minx, miny, maxx, maxy = gdf_district_northern.total_bounds
    ax.set_xlim(minx, maxx)
    ax.set_ylim(miny, maxy)

    geopt_cluster4.plot(ax = ax, color = "royalblue", markersize = 0.5, marker= "o", label="potential location")


    # Get the handles and labels from the current axes
    handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
    # Add the handles and labels from the second legend to the first one
    handles += patches
    labels += legend_name

    pos = ax.get_position()
    #ax.set_position([pos.x0, pos.y0, pos.width * 0.9, pos.height])
    ax.legend(loc='center right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.2, 0.8), handles=handles, labels=labels)
    #ax.legend(handles, labels)
    plt.title(f"Potential Locations to Build Fire Stations in {conversion.get(city_name)}")
    plt.show()

def unsatisfied_accident_location(df_list, city_name, incident_loca):
    legend_name = ["brigade 1", "brigade 2", "brigade 3", "brigade 4", "brigade 5", "brigade 6", "brigade 7"]
    color = ["springgreen", "lightgreen", "plum", "lightblue", "cyan", "aliceblue", "lightpink"]
    conversion = {'桃園市': "Taoyuan City", "臺北市": "Taipei City", "新北市": "New Taipei City", "基隆市": "Keelung City"}
    legend_name = ["brigade 1", "brigade 2", "brigade 3", "brigade 4", "brigade 5", "brigade 6", "brigade 7"]
    
    station_x, station_Y = return_XY(incident_loca)
    cluster_station = [Point(xy) for xy in zip(station_x, station_Y)]
    geopt_cluster4 = gp.GeoDataFrame(incident_loca, geometry=cluster_station)
    gdf_district_northern = gdf_district[gdf_district.COUNTYNAME.isin([city_name])]
    ax = gdf_district_northern.plot()
    patches = []
    for i in range(len(df_list)):
        gdf_district_northern[gdf_district_northern.TOWNNAME.isin(df_list[i])].plot(edgecolor=u'gray', color=color[i], ax=ax)
        patches.append(mpatches.Patch(color=color[i], label=legend_name[i]))
    minx, miny, maxx, maxy = gdf_district_northern.total_bounds
    ax.set_xlim(minx, maxx)
    ax.set_ylim(miny, maxy)

    geopt_cluster4.plot(ax = ax, color = "red", markersize = 0.5, marker= "o", label="incident location")


    # Get the handles and labels from the current axes
    handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
    # Add the handles and labels from the second legend to the first one
    handles += patches
    labels += legend_name

    pos = ax.get_position()
    ax.set_position([pos.x0, pos.y0, pos.width * 0.9, pos.height])
    ax.legend(loc='center right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.4, 0.5), handles=handles, labels=labels)
    ax.legend(handles, labels)
    plt.title(f"Unsatisfied incident location in {conversion.get(city_name)}")
    plt.show()

variable definition and model¶

paramters¶

$$ \begin{align*} I &: \text{the set of fire stations} \\ J & : \text{the set of accident locations} \\ Q^F & : \text{fire rescue quota per day} \\ Q^A & : \text{ambulance quota per day} \\ %D_j & : \text{date of accident } j, j \in J \\ %F_i & : \text{fire station } i, i \in I \\ H_{ij} & : \text{distance between fire station } i \text{ and accident location } j \\ R_j^F & : \text{requirement of fire quota for accident } j, j \in J \\ R_j^A & : \text{requirement of ambulance quota for accident } j, j \in J \\ B_{ij} & : \text{whether fire station } i \text{ can go to rescue accident } j, i \in I, j \in J \\ A_{jd} & : \text{whether accident } j \text{ happens on day } d, j \in J, d \in D \\ M_{} & : \text{is the upper bound } \\ F_{} & : \frac{1}{\left | I \right | \left | J \right | H} \text{ where H is} \max_{(i,j) \text{ }\in \text{ } I \times J}H_{ij} \\ \end{align*} $$

decision variables¶

$$ \begin{align*} a_{ij} &: \text{whether to send squad in fire station } i \text{ to accident } j, i \in I, j \in J \\ x_{ij} &: \text{amount of ambulance for fire station } i \text{ to send to accident } j, \forall i \in I,j \in J \\ s_j & : \text{whether the accident } j \text{ is rescued within } P \text{ km} \text{ for } j \in J\\ y_{ij} & : \text{whether } a_{ij} H_{ij} \leq P \text{ for a given pair } (i, j) \text{ for } i \in I, j \in J \\ z_{i} &: \text{whether the station is built at location } i\\ \end{align*} $$

formulation¶

$$ \max \sum_{j \in J} s_j - F\sum_{i \in I} \sum_{j \in J} a_{ij} H_{ij} \quad \\ $$

subject to the following constraints:

$$ \begin{align} \sum_{j}a_{ij}^F \leq 10^6 z_i \quad\\ \sum_{i}z_i \leq 10 \quad\\ a_{ij} H_{ij} \leq P + M(1-y_{ij}) \quad \forall i \in I, j \in J \quad \\ s_j \leq \sum_{i \in I} y_{ij} \quad \forall j \in J \quad \\ \sum_{j \in J} a_{ij} A_{jd} \leq Q^F \quad \forall i \in I, d \in D \quad \\ \sum_{a_{ij}} \geq R_j r_j \quad\\ s_j \leq r_j \quad\\ a_{ij} \leq B_{ij} \quad \forall i \in I, j \in J \quad \\ a_{ij} \in \{0, 1\} \quad \forall i \in I, j \in J \quad\\ y_{ij} \in \{0, 1\} \quad \forall i \in I, j \in J \quad\\ \quad s_j \in \{0, 1\} \quad \forall j \in J \quad \end{align} $$

Q_fd = 6 # fire rescue quota a day # 2
Q_ad = 24 # ambulance quota a day # 8
MAX_STA = 5
days = range(1, 367)
D_j = df_incident["day_happen"].to_list()
R_jf = df_incident["fire_reqr"].tolist()
R_ja = df_incident["ambulance_reqr"].tolist()
num_inc = len(df_incident)
num_sta = len(df_station)

construct H_ij, A_jd, B_ij¶

let $I$ be set of fire stations, $J$ be set of incident location, and $D$ be set of days, $D \in \{1, ...,366\}$ $$ \begin{align*} H_{ij} &: \text{the distance between fire station } i \text{ to incident location } j \\ A_{jd} &: \text{whether the incident } j \text{ happens at day } d \\ B_{ij} &: \text{whether fire station } i \text{can save incident location }j \\ \end{align*} $$

In [20]:
# H_ij
H_ij = np.zeros((num_sta, num_inc))
for i in range(num_sta):
    for j in range(num_inc):
        coords_1 = (df_station["wgs84aY"][i], df_station["wgs84aX"][i]) # fire station i
        coords_2 = (df_incident["wgs84aY"][j], df_incident["wgs84aX"][j]) # incident location j
        #print(coords_1, coords_2)
        dist = geopy.distance.geodesic(coords_1, coords_2).m
        H_ij[i, j]= dist

# A_jd
A_jd = {}
for j in range(num_inc):
    for d in range(1, 367):
        if d == int(df_incident["day_happen"][j]):
            #print(d, int(df_incident["day_happen"][j]))
            A_jd[j,d] = 1
        else:
            A_jd[j,d] = 0

# B_ij
B_ij = np.zeros((num_sta, num_inc))
for i in range(num_sta):
    for j in range(num_inc):
        if int(df_station["cluster"][i]) == int(df_incident["cluster"][j]):
            B_ij[i,j] = 1
        else:
            B_ij[i,j] = 0

m3 = Model("FTP_part3")
P = 5500 # 65km/h = 1080m/min (approx 5 mins)
a_ijf3 = {}
c_idf3 = {}
s_j = {}
y_ij = {}
z_i = {}
for i in range(num_sta):
    z_i[i] = m3.addVar(vtype = GRB.BINARY, name="z_%d"%i)
    for j in range(num_inc):
        a_ijf3[i,j] = m3.addVar(vtype = GRB.BINARY, name="a_%d_%d_f3"%(i, j))
        #x_ija2[i,j] = m3.addVar(vtype = GRB.INTEGER, lb = 0, name="x_%d%d_a2"%(i, j))
        y_ij[i,j] = m3.addVar(vtype = GRB.BINARY, name="y_%d_%d_a"%(i, j))
    
for i in range(num_sta):
    for d in days:
        c_idf3[i,d] = m3.addVar(vtype = GRB.INTEGER, lb = 0, name="c_%d_%d_f3"%(i, d))
        #c_ida2[i,d] = m3.addVar(vtype = GRB.INTEGER, lb = 0, name="c_%d%d_a2"%(i, d))

for j in range(num_inc):
    s_j[j] = m3.addVar(vtype = GRB.BINARY, name="s_%d_f"%j)

m3.setObjective(100000* quicksum(s_j[j] for j in range(num_inc)) - quicksum(quicksum(a_ijf3[i,j]* H_ij[i,j] for i in range(num_sta))for j in range(num_inc)) ,GRB.MAXIMIZE) # 
# constraint
for i in range(num_sta):
    m3.addConstr( quicksum(a_ijf3[i,j] for j in range(num_inc)) <= 2000000 * z_i[i]) # NEW
    for d in days:
        m3.addConstr(c_idf3[i,d] <= Q_fd)
        m3.addConstr(c_idf3[i,d] == quicksum(a_ijf3[i,j]*A_jd[j,d] for j in range(num_inc)))
        


for j in range(num_inc):
    m3.addConstr(quicksum(a_ijf3[i,j] for i in range(num_sta)) <= R_jf[j])
    m3.addConstr(s_j[j] <= quicksum(y_ij[i,j] for i in range(num_sta)))
    #m3.addConstr(quicksum(x_ija2[i,j] for i in range(num_sta)) >= R_ja[j])

for i in range(num_sta):
    for j in range(num_inc):
        m3.addConstr(a_ijf3[i,j] <= B_ij[i,j])
        m3.addConstr(y_ij[i,j] <= B_ij[i,j]) # NEW
        m3.addConstr(y_ij[i,j] <= a_ijf3[i,j]) # NEW
        #m2.addConstr(x_ija2[i,j] <= R_ja[j] * B_ij[i,j])
        m3.addConstr(a_ijf3[i,j]*H_ij[i,j] <= (P + 2000000 * (1 - y_ij[i,j])) )
        
m3.addConstr(quicksum(z_i[i] for i in range(num_sta)) <= MAX_STA) # NEW

    cluster2 = [Point(xy) for xy in zip(cluster2_x, cluster2_Y)]
    cluster3 = [Point(xy) for xy in zip(cluster3_x, cluster3_Y)]

    geopt_cluster1 = gp.GeoDataFrame(sat_inc, geometry=cluster1)
    geopt_cluster2 = gp.GeoDataFrame(sat_sta, geometry=cluster2)

    gdf_district_northern = gdf_district[gdf_district.COUNTYNAME.isin([city])]
    ax = gdf_district_northern.plot()

    for i in range(len(df_list)):
        #print(i)
        gdf_district_northern[gdf_district_northern.TOWNNAME.isin(df_list[i])].plot(edgecolor=u'gray', color=color[i], ax=ax)

# new value
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# Define the data
categories = ['Keelung', 'New Taipei', 'Taipei', 'Taoyuan']
constrained = [1929.871633,	2497.022687, 1685.473306, 3992.336619]
unconstrained = [1808.217479, 2275.425031, 1546.438172, 3599.166177]



# Set the position of the bars on the x-axis
x = np.arange(len(categories))
bar_width = 0.35

# Create the grouped bar chart
plt.bar(x - bar_width/2, constrained, width=bar_width, label='Constrained')
plt.bar(x + bar_width/2, unconstrained, width=bar_width, label='Unconstrained')

# Set labels and title
plt.xlabel('City')
plt.ylabel('Distance')
# comparison of distance travelled between unconstrained and constrained model in Taipei Metric Zone
plt.title('Comparison of Distance Travelled between Unconstrained \n and Constrained Model in Taipei Metropolitan Area')
plt.xticks(x, categories)
plt.legend()

# Display the chart
plt.show()
